  "text": "With minor simplifications, such solvers (e.g. for the MULTICUT problem) can be formalized as maps that take continuous input y ∈ R n (e.g. edge weights of a fixed graph) and return discrete output s ∈ S ⊂ R n (e.g. indicator vector of a subset of edges forming a cut) such that it minimizes a combinatorial objective expressed as an inner product y · s (e.g. the cost of the cut). Note that the notation differs from [CITATION_1] (y was w and s was y). In short, a blackbox solver is",
